    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n3904" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εὖ, ἐύ</span></b>  (neut. of <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐύς</span>): <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">well</span>, answering in
          meaning as adv. to the adjectives <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀγαθός</span> and <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κᾱλός</span>; hence
          ‘rightly,’ ‘finely,’ ‘carefully,’ etc., esp. ‘happily,’
          ‘prosperously,’ <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εὖ ζώειν, εὖ οἴκαδ᾽
            ἱκέσθαι,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Od. 17.423</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 1.19</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 3.188</span></i>,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc"> 190; εὖ ἔρδειν τινά</span>, i. e. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀγαθὰ ἔρδειν</span>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            5.650</span></i>; used to strengthen other words, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εὖ</span>
          
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μάλα, εὖ πάντες</span>, ‘quite all,’ <i><span class="en">Od. 10.452</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od.
            18.260</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
